Congressman Don McEachin of Virginia has passed away after battling cancer. The author expresses sadness and offers condolences to Don's wife and children. Don was known for his friendship and support, particularly during the author's presidential campaign. He was a strong advocate for justice, civil rights, and marginalized communities. Don's leadership resulted in the passage of significant legislation addressing the climate crisis and environmental justice. Having a background in public service, Don tirelessly fought for the working people of Virginia. The author concludes by sending blessings to Don's family.